4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper involves optimization of a submodular function, which is a common technique in machine learning. This makes it likely to belong to the cs.LG sub-category.
5. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper involves characterizing positivity of eigenvalues using probability distributions, which is a concept related to information theory. This makes it possible for the paper to belong to the cs.IT sub-category.
